The epic document has been written to `/home/stephan/src/FairEmail/docs/epics/7.5-offline-storage-and-operations.md`. It covers:

- **Background & Purpose** — why offline operation queuing is foundational
- **Goals / Non-Goals** — scoped to queuing and replay, excluding sync scheduling and full-text search
- **Glossary** — key terms (operation, replay, optimistic UI, transient/permanent failure)
- **Personas** — commuter, traveler, triage-heavy user, power user
- **User Stories** — 20 stories across local acceptance, replay, offline reading, error handling, queue management, and conflict resolution
- **Functional Requirements** — 40 requirements covering operation creation, supported types, priority ordering, replay/batching, retry logic, conflict resolution, duplicate suppression, queue management UI, and local content storage
- **Non-Functional Requirements** — responsiveness, durability, scalability, convergence, idempotency, transparency, data integrity, storage efficiency
- **Acceptance Criteria** — 18 testable criteria
- **Open Questions** — 8 genuine ambiguities discovered during analysis
- **Design Notes & Rationale** — 7 architectural decisions implicit in the source
